The paper proposes a deep learning approach for change detection in SAR images, which involves object-based segmentation and classification using fuzzy c-means and PCANet. This methodology is related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves deep learning techniques. Additionally, the use of fuzzy c-means and segmentation algorithms suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper also involves signal processing techniques such as low rank and sparse decomposition, which suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
